<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Wanderly</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h3>Listing Details : </h3>
    <ul>
        <li><%= listing.title %></li>
        <li><%= listing.description %></li>
        <li>&#8377; <%= listing.price.toLocaleString("en-IN") %></li>
        <!-- 
            1. toLocaleString() is a JavaScript method used to convert values (like Date, Number, Array) into a human-readable string based on local language & region format.
            2. In our case,it converts price in number format into a string seperated by coma based on indian representation (eg : 10,25,357)
        -->
        <li><%= listing.country %></li>
        <!-- <li></li> -->
    </ul>
</body>
</html>